.TH MCOOKIE 1 "June 2026" "svr4_utils" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mcookie \- generate a magic cookie for xauth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcookie
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcookie
prints a random hexadecimal cookie suitable for use with
.BR xauth (1).
In this SVR4 port, the command keeps a small compatibility surface rather than
mirroring every util-linux detail.
.PP
If no seed file is supplied, a cookie is generated from
.BR /dev/urandom ,
with
.BR /dev/random
used as a fallback.
If a seed file is given with
.BR -f ,
its contents are mixed into the generated cookie.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -f , " --file "\fIfile\fP
Use \fIfile\fP as a cookie seed.
.TP
.BR -m , " --max-size "\fInum\fP
Limit how much data is read from the seed file.
Common binary suffixes such as KiB and MiB are accepted.
.TP
.BR -v , " --verbose"
Describe what is being done.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Display help and exit.
.TP
.BR -V , " --version"
Display version information and exit.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xauth (1)
